im scared to go out in public i get really nervous and i feel really insecure when i have to go somewhere my best friend moved at the beginning of the summer we did everything together and thats when i stopped going out of the house i have other friends too but i didn't talk to them all summer they would call my house and i would never answer because i got to scared to talk to them just recently i talked on the phone with closer friend and we were going to do something together but she is going out of state tomorrow so i'm pretty much back to square one i'm moving to a new state next week and i have to make a trip to the mall sometime soon i am absolutely devastated i'm so scared to talk to someone or for someone to recognize me my hands are shaking just thinking about it in a few hours i have to go to the computer store with my mom i'm sixteen to get my laptop fixed and i am dreading it i'm so nervous i don't know what to do does anyone have any advice tips or any help at all mainly going off what they said i went through a stretch of about a year where i went through exactly the same problems you are stress is a common reason for things like this at least in my case i try to either release my stress or try to control it my doctor prescribed me zoloft and it has really helped me socially i am more confident especially around girls still working on getting my first girlfriend though lol and i am enjoying public it did not work all at first it took my own patience and effort to go out and do it no matter how bad i would feel it's a battle and it will be tough but you can do it but of course talk to your doctor first they're the ones that got to college for a decade hope i helped Avenue Q Shaggy dog story The Ashlee Simpson Show EastEnders Theory of conduct Jean Grey 2000 Australian Grand Prix Kodocha Social rule Oasis (band) The Inside Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Spice Girls Coming of Age (TNG episode) Milton H. Erickson The Emancipation of Mimi Undergrads Boston Public S